text:
Not exactly sure where to post this so I’m going to shoot for here. This morning our menu just broke. No one has touched it in a month. Seems styling isn’t being applied I have been able to track down some errors in the console log referencing ‘application/json’ not being supported. I’m very baffled at what it could be referencing. Any help would be appriciated.

Refused to apply style from ‘<https://www.theoperationscompany.com/hs-fs/hubfs/hub_generated/module_assets/1/142712586671/1735860358381/module_th-hero-2.min.css>’ because its MIME type (‘application/json’) is not a supported stylesheet MIME type, and strict MIME checking is enabled.
Also when I review the theme in the theme editor it looks fine and doesn’t have the errors in the console log either. I tried republishing but that didn’t help.

Strange things can happen with HubSpot + Cloudflare, sometimes best thing is to re-upload images/files.

In this case check module-button and module-section, could be someone renamed, changed label or ID of module...
• if you have files in your browser: download them if they are not in `Module` or `Design Manager` 
Do they have something in common? deleted macro or ?
